class Solution {
public:
    int majorityElement(vector<int>& nums) {
        int n = nums.size();
        map<int,int>mp;
        for(int i = 0;i<n;i++){
            mp[nums[i]]++;
        }
        int ans = -1;
        for(auto&i:mp){
            if(i.second>(n/2)){
                ans = i.first;
            }
        }
        return ans;
    }
};


"Idea:
Create a map mp to store the frequency of each element in the array.
Traverse the array and increment the count of every number using mp[nums[i]]++.
After counting frequencies, iterate through the map.
Check if any element appears more than n/2 times, where n is the size of the array.
The element satisfying this condition is the majority element.
Store that element in ans and return it at the end.
Time Complexity: O(n log n) because map operations take O(log n) time, and Space Complexity: O(n) for storing frequencies.
"
